==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redolent
<hw>Red"o*lent</hw> <pr>(-l<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>redolens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>redolere</ets> to
emit a scent, diffuse an odor; pref. <ets>red-</ets>, <ets>re-</ets>,
re- + <ets>olere</ets> to emit a smell. See <er>Odor</er>.]</ety>
<def>Diffusing odor or fragrance; spreading sweet scent; scented;
odorous; smelling; -- usually followed by <xex>of</xex>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Honey <xex>redolent</xex> of spring.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Dryden.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Red"o*lent*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gales . . . <qex>redolent</qex> of joy and youth.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redouble</ent>⟦br⟧
